headlines.description: Jarvis Landry made a spectacular one-handed touchdown catch and No. 8 LSU kept its BCS hopes alive with a 20-13 win over Arkansas on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: LSU hangs on, remains alive in BCS

headlines.description: Rex Burkhead scored the go-ahead touchdown in his return from a knee injury and Nebraska (No. 14 BCS, No. 17 AP) beat Iowa 13-7 on Friday to claim the Legends Division's berth in the championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burkhead returns, helps Nebraska top Iowa

events.name: Ohio Bobcats at Kent State Golden Flashes

headlines.description: C.J. Malauulu returned an interception 33 yards for a touchdown -- 12 seconds after another Kent State TD -- and the No. 23 Golden Flashes completed a perfect season in the Mid-American Conference by beating Ohio, 28-6.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 23 Kent St. downs Ohio, now 8-0 in MAC

events.name: Arizona State Sun Devils at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Marion Grice ran for 156 yards and three touchdowns, and Arizona State added another chapter to what's become a wild rivalry by scoring 24 points in the fourth quarter to beat Arizona 41-34 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: ASU scores 24 in fourth to rally vs. Arizona

events.name: Washington Huskies at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Andrew Furney kicked a 27-yard field goal on Washington State's first possession of overtime, and the Cougars overcame an 18-point deficit in the fourth quarter to stun rival Washington 31-28 in the Apple Cup on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wash. St. snaps 8-game skid, wins Apple Cup

headlines.description: Ryan Nassib threw for 215 yards and a touchdown, and Adonis Aimeen-Moore rushed for a pair of scores to lead Syracuse to a 38-20 victory over Temple on Friday in the Orange's last Big East game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cuse runs past Temple in final Big East game

events.name: Ball State Cardinals at Miami (OH) RedHawks

headlines.description: Jahwan Edwards rushed for three touchdowns as Ball State defeated Miami (Ohio) 31-24 Friday in their regular-season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball St. defeats Miami (Ohio) to win 6th straight

events.name: Northern Illinois Huskies at Eastern Michigan Eagles

headlines.description: Akeem Daniels scored a career-best four touchdowns and Northern Illinois ended its regular season with its 11th straight victory, 49-7 against Eastern Michigan on a cold and snowy Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daniels runs for 4 TDs; N. Illinois gets 11th win

events.name: Marshall Thundering Herd at East Carolina Pirates
Buffalo Bulls at Bowling Green Falcons

headlines.description: Reggie Dunn responded to Marques Mosley's 100-yard kickoff return for a touchdown with one of his own 13 seconds later, and Utah used five takeaways to outlast Colorado 42-35 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah uses five turnovers to outlast Colorado

events.name: Central Michigan Chippewas at UMass Minutemen
West Virginia Mountaineers at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Tavon Austin turned a touch pass from Geno Smith into a 75-yard touchdown with 6:31 left and West Virginia held on to beat Iowa State 31-24 Friday to break a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: WVU downs Iowa St. to snap five-game skid

events.name: South Florida Bulls at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Brendon Kay threw for a touchdown and ran for another on Friday night, getting Cincinnati's offense moving again after its worst showing of the season, and the Bearcats pulled away to a 27-10 victory over South Florida.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cincy rebounds from worst showing of season
